description: North Carolina Lt. Gov. Mark Robinson denies reports of disturbing comments; Lebanon hit with Israeli airstrikes today following device explosions; One group's mission against underwater garbage; and more on tonight’s broadcast.

description: We heard new and emotional testimony today during a U.S. Coast Guard hearing about the doomed Titan submersible. The Titan imploded last year as it descended to the site of the Titanic wreckage. Five people aboard were killed. There's also newly-released footage showing the debris from that implosion on the ocean floor. NBC News' Jesse Kirsch reports.
title: U.S. Coast Guard hears testimony about the doomed Titan submersible

description: We meet a group of women aged 64 to 84 making it their mission to clean up the waters in Cape Cod. They call themselves the Old Ladies Against Underwater Garbage scouring more than 200 freshwater ponds for pieces of trash. NBC News' Stephanie Gosk has their story.
